config ZMK_LAYOUT_INDICATORS
    bool "Layout indicator LEDs controlled by a paired host over BLE"
    depends on ZMK_BLE
    default y
    help
      Registers a custom BLE GATT service with one writable, encryption-required
      characteristic. A paired host (the companion app) writes a single byte to
      select which keyboard-layout indicator LED is lit:

          0 = US  (led_us on,  led_ua off)
          1 = UA  (led_ua on,  led_us off)
          2 = off / unknown (both off)

      Requires the board to define `led_us` and `led_ua` GPIO nodelabels (see the
      crabulik_console shield overlay).
